ist[BuiltIn]` — required opening tasks, run in order\n   - `close: list[BuiltIn]` — required closing tasks, run in order\n   - `middle_kinds: list[type]` — allowed task types in the middle (e.g. `[AgentTask, ShellTask]`)\n   - `middle_required: dict[type, tuple[int, int | None]]` — minimum/maximum count constraints per task type\n2. Implement `.compose(name, description, applies_to, priority, middle)` that:\n   - Validates every task in `middle` is an instance of one of `middle_kinds`; raises `TemplateViolation` if not\n   - Validates `middle_required` count constraints; raises `TemplateViolation` if violated\n   - Returns a `Workflow` with tasks `[*self.open, *middle, *self.close]`\n   - Sets `template_name` on the resulting `Workflow`\n3. Add a `template_name: str | None = None` field to `Workflow`.\n4. Define `TemplateViolation` as a clear, user-facing exception with a message explaining what constraint was violated.\n5. Handle the module naming collision: the existing `templates.py` handles prompt templates — either rename it to `prompts.py` or name the new module `workflow_templates.py`. Choose whichever minimizes churn.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### New module: `src/darkfactory/templates.py`\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Callable\n\nfrom .workflow import Workflow, BuiltIn, AgentTask, ShellTask\n\n\nclass TemplateViolation(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a composed middle violates the template's constraints.\"\"\"\n\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass WorkflowTemplate:\n    name: str\n    description: str\n    open: list[BuiltIn]\n    close: list[BuiltIn]\n    middle_kinds: list[type] = field(default_factory=list)\n    middle_required: dict[type, tuple[int, int | None]] = field(default_factory=dict)\n\n    def compose(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        description: str,\n        applies_to: Callable,\n        priority: int,\n        middle: list,\n    ) -> Workflow:\n        self._validate_middle(middle)\n        return Workflow(\n            name=name,\n            description=description,\n            applies_to=applies_to,\n            priority=priority,\n            tasks=[*self.open, *middle, *self.close],\n            template_name=self.name,\n        )\n\n    def _validate_middle(self, middle: list) -> None:\n        # Check kinds\n        for task in middle:\n            if not isinstance(task, tuple(self.middle_kinds)):\n                raise TemplateViolation(\n                    f\"Task {task!r} is not an allowed middle kind \"\n                    f\"(allowed: {[k.__name__ for k in self.middle_kinds]})\"\n                )\n        # Check required counts\n        for kind, (min_count, max_count) in self.middle_required.items():\n            actual = sum(1 for t in middle if isinstance(t, kind))\n            if actual < min_count:\n                raise TemplateViolation(\n                    f\"Template requires at least {min_count} {kind.__name__} \"\n                    f\"in the middle, got {actual}\"\n                )\n            if max_count is not None and actual > max_count:\n                raise TemplateViolation(\n                    f\"Template allows at most {max_count} {kind.__name__} \"\n                    f\"in the middle, got {actual}\"\n                )\n```\n\n### Workflow modification: `src/darkfactory/workflow.py`\n\nAdd `template_name: str | None = None` to the `Workflow` dataclass.\n\n### Tests: `tests/test_workflow_templates.py`\n\n- Test valid composition produces correct task ordering\n- Test `template_name` is set on composed workflow\n- Test `TemplateViolation` for disallowed task kinds\n- Test `TemplateViolation` for count constraint violations (too few, too many)\n- Test that `Workflow` without a template has `template_name = None`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `WorkflowTemplate.compose(middle=[...])` produces a `Workflow` whose tasks are `[*open, *middle, *close]`.\n- [ ] AC-2: Composing with a middle that violates `middle_kinds` raises `TemplateViolation` with a clear message.\n- [ ] AC-3: Composing with a middle that violates `middle_required` raises `TemplateViolation` with a clear message.\n- [ ] AC-4: The composed workflow exposes `template_name` matching the template's `name`.\n- [ ] AC-5: Existing `Workflow(tasks=[...])` construction still works with `template_name` defaulting to `None`.\n- [ ] AC-6: Test coverage for all validation paths (valid, invalid kind, too few, too many).\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KhnKttzdt6xTvRkYGMTo8e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BUFyYiWU2Qpt47GGpuaFGw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-227-workflow-templates/prds/PRD-227.2-prd-implementation-template.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-227.2\"\ntitle: \"Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: high\neffort: xs\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.3-migrate-default-workflow]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-227.4-migrate-extraction-workflow]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - workflow\n---\n\n# Provide PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE\n\n## Summary\n\nBundle a built-in `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` that captures the standard PRD implementation lifecycle with PRD-224 invariants enforced. This is the template that most workflows will compose from. It is a declarative definition — the BuiltIns it references either already exist or are introduced by PRD-224.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py` containing `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n2. The template's opening tasks enforce:\n   - `ensure_worktree` (PRD-217 lock + PRD-224.2 stale check)\n   - `set_status(to=\"in-progress\")`\n   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\")`\n3. The template's closing tasks enforce:\n   - `summarize_agent_run` (PRD-224.3)\n   - `commit_transcript` (PRD-224.6)\n   - `set_status(to=\"review\")`\n   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\")`\n   - `push_branch`\n   - `create_pr`\n4. The middle requires at least 1 `AgentTask` and at least 1 `ShellTask`.\n5. The template is importable: `from darkfactory.templates_builtin import PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .templates import WorkflowTemplate\nfrom .workflow import BuiltIn, AgentTask, ShellTask\n\nPRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n    name=\"prd-implementation\",\n    description=\"Standard PRD implementation lifecycle with enforced invariants.\",\n    open=[\n        BuiltIn(\"ensure_worktree\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"in-progress\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} start work\"}),\n    ],\n    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n    middle_required={\n        AgentTask: (1, None),\n        ShellTask: (1, None),\n    },\n    close=[\n        BuiltIn(\"summarize_agent_run\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit_transcript\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"review\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} ready for review\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"push_branch\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"create_pr\"),\n    ],\n)\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `PRD_IMPLEMENTATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n- [ ] AC-2: The template's `open` list contains `ensure_worktree`, `set_status(in-progress)`, and `commit(start work)` in that order.\n- [ ] AC-3: The template's `close` list contains all PRD-224 invariant tasks (`summarize_agent_run`, `commit_transcript`, `set_status(review)`, `commit(ready for review)`, `push_branch`, `create_pr`) in that order.\n- [ ] AC-4: Composing with no `AgentTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n- [ ] AC-5: Composing with no `ShellTask` in the middle raises `TemplateViolation`.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":916,"cache_read_input_tokens":27003,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":916},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":