{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KhnKttzdt6xTvRkYGMTo8e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01K4v4vrb4eaaZVjL9vcvRzF","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-227-workflow-templates/prds/PRD-227.5-rework-template.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-227.5\"\ntitle: \"Define REWORK_TEMPLATE\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\n  - tests/test_workflow_templates.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - workflow\n---\n\n# Define REWORK_TEMPLATE\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine `REWORK_TEMPLATE` for the rework/revision workflow that PRD-225 introduces. The rework template differs from implementation: it opens by checking that a PR exists, resuming the worktree, and fetching review comments; it closes by committing and pushing to the existing branch (no `create_pr`). This template enforces rework-specific invariants by construction.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Define `REWORK_TEMPLATE` in `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`.\n2. Opening tasks:\n   - `check_pr_exists` — assert the PR is open and fetch its URL\n   - `resume_worktree` — resume (not create) the existing worktree\n   - `fetch_review_comments` — pull PR review comments for context\n   - `set_status(to=\"in-progress\")`\n3. Closing tasks:\n   - `summarize_agent_run`\n   - `commit_transcript`\n   - `set_status(to=\"review\")`\n   - `commit(message=\"chore(prd): {prd_id} address review feedback\")`\n   - `push_branch` (no `create_pr` — PR already exists)\n4. Middle requires at least 1 `AgentTask`.\n5. Add tests for the rework template's compose/validation behavior.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n\n```python\nREWORK_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n    name=\"rework\",\n    description=\"Rework lifecycle: resume existing PR, address feedback, push updates.\",\n    open=[\n        BuiltIn(\"check_pr_exists\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"resume_worktree\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"fetch_review_comments\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"in-progress\"}),\n    ],\n    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n    middle_required={\n        AgentTask: (1, None),\n    },\n    close=[\n        BuiltIn(\"summarize_agent_run\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit_transcript\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"set_status\", kwargs={\"to\": \"review\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"commit\", kwargs={\"message\": \"chore(prd): {prd_id} address review feedback\"}),\n        BuiltIn(\"push_branch\"),\n    ],\n)\n```\n\n### Tests\n\n- Valid rework composition produces correct task order\n- Missing `AgentTask` in middle raises `TemplateViolation`\n- Closing does not include `create_pr`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `REWORK_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n- [ ] AC-2: The template's close list does NOT include `create_pr`.\n- [ ] AC-3: The template's open list includes `check_pr_exists` and `fetch_review_comments`.\n- [ ] AC-4: Composing with no `AgentTask` raises `TemplateViolation`.\n- [ ] AC-5: Test coverage for valid and invalid rework compositions.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":916,"cache_read_input_tokens":27003,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":916},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6e45125-65ac-4a6b-991e-ec8e60826033","uuid":"0ee75099-7f6f-4d7d-b175-d1ecbab70f9a"}
