o minimum count constraints (some system ops may be pure shell).\n5. Add tests for the system operation template's compose/validation behavior.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n\n```python\nSYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n    name=\"system-operation\",\n    description=\"System operation lifecycle: lock, execute, report, unlock.\",\n    open=[\n        BuiltIn(\"acquire_global_lock\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_start\"),\n    ],\n    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n    middle_required={},\n    close=[\n        BuiltIn(\"write_report\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_end\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"release_global_lock\"),\n    ],\n)\n```\n\n### Tests\n\n- Valid composition produces `[lock, log_start, *middle, report, log_end, unlock]`\n- Empty middle is allowed (middle_required is empty)\n- Disallowed task types in middle raise `TemplateViolation`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n- [ ] AC-2: The template's close list includes `release_global_lock` as the final task.\n- [ ] AC-3: The template's open list includes `acquire_global_lock` as the first task.\n- [ ] AC-4: Composing with an empty middle succeeds (no minimum count constraints).\n- [ ] AC-5: Test coverage for valid composition and kind violations.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
